    "caption": "The biggest, loudest parrot in the jungle, coloured like a flying sunset.",
    "shortDescription": "Macaws are the largest parrots in the world, with beaks so strong they can crack open a Brazil nut — one of the hardest seeds on Earth. They fly through the Amazon rainforest in noisy pairs, and their screaming calls carry for kilometres. Macaws visit clay riverbanks to eat mineral-rich mud — the minerals help neutralise toxins in the seeds they eat. Fun fact: Macaws often mate for life and spend almost all their time with the same partner."
